    "title": "Samaria — שֹׁמְרוֹן (Shomron)",
    "description": "Omri purchases the hill and names the city after its previous owner, Shemer. The city will endure for centuries and become synonymous with the northern kingdom of Israel. When later prophets speak of \"Samaria,\" they mean the entire rebellious northern kingdom.",
    "bookSlug": "1-kings",
    "chapter": 16,
    "language": "hebrew"
