    "script": "פָּסַח",
    "translit": "<strong>Pesach</strong> · to limp; to halt; to waver between two paths",
    "title": "Pesach — \"To Halt/Limp\"",
    "description": "The verb Elijah uses—\"halt ye between two opinions\"—carries the image of a creature limping, unable to move forward decisively. It is not a neutral stance. It is a kind of spiritual injury, a people unable to commit, unable to walk securely in any direction. This same verb root later becomes Passover (Pesach), where God \"passes over\" the homes of the faithful.",
    "bookSlug": "1-kings",
