    "script": "דַּיָּה",
    "translit": "<strong>Dayyah</strong> · it is enough; sufficient; used in resignation and closure",
    "title": "דַּיָּה <em>Dayyah</em> — \"It is Enough\"",
    "description": "The word \"dayyah\" carries the weight of finality. It is the word a person speaks when they have come to the end of something — when endurance is exhausted, when they cannot go further. Elijah does not say \"I am tired\" or \"I am afraid.\" He says \"it is enough\" — as though his very existence has become a burden too great to bear.",
