    "title": "אַדֶּ֫רֶת <em>Adderet</em> — \"Mantle\" or \"Cloak\"",
    "description": "The mantle is Elijah&apos;s symbol of office — the mark of the prophet. When he casts it upon Elisha, he is not simply offering a garment; he is offering a calling. The mantle is the visible sign of an invisible commission. To receive the mantle is to accept the burden and the grace of being God&apos;s spokesman.",
    "bookSlug": "1-kings",
