    "title": "בֶּן־הֲדַד — Ben-hadad",
    "description": "Ben-hadad&apos;s name itself is a claim to divine power. Hadad was the Syrian storm god, bringer of rain and military victory. Ben-hadad presents himself as the chosen son of divine power. Yet this chapter will demonstrate that his power, great as it is, is no match for the God of Israel.",
