    "translit": "<strong>Cherem</strong> · devoted destruction; sacred war; curse",
    "title": "חֵ֫רֶם — Cherem: \"Devoted Destruction\"",
    "description": "Ben-hadad has been marked for cherem — devoted destruction — by the God of Israel. This is not merely military defeat. This is the sacred consequence of standing against the Lord. Cherem appears throughout Israel&apos;s holy war traditions: nations marked for destruction are given over completely to the judgment of God. That Ben-hadad survives this chapter is a mercy he will not deserve when his ultimate reckoning comes.",
