    "translit": "<strong>Kanaf</strong> (related) · to go humbly; to walk in submission",
    "title": "Kanaf — \"To Go Softly\"",
    "description": "The word \"went softly\" carries the sense of walking humbly, of moving with the posture of one who has been broken. Ahab is no longer the king who demands. He is a man who has seen his own evil and cannot stand upright before God.",
    "bookSlug": "1-kings",
    "chapter": 21,
    "language": "hebrew"
