    "translit": "<strong>Kerem</strong> · vineyard; a plot of land planted with vines",
    "title": "Kerem — \"Vineyard\"",
    "description": "The vineyard is not merely a possession. In the language of Scripture, a vineyard is a sign of God&apos;s care and blessing—a place of productivity, of life-giving fruit. To have a vineyard is to be rooted, to be blessed, to belong to the land. Naboth&apos;s vineyard, his family&apos;s kerem, is a legacy. It is not a commodity.",
