    "title": "Nachalah — \"Inheritance\"",
    "description": "The word nachalah carries the sense of something that is yours by covenant, by family, by God&apos;s distribution of the land. It is not earned or bought. It is inherited, held in trust for the next generation. To take a nachalah from someone is to break the covenant structure of Israel itself.",
    "bookSlug": "1-kings",
    "chapter": 21,
    "language": "hebrew"
