    "title": "A Man After His Own Heart — אִישׁ כִּלְבָבוֹ",
    "description": "The phrase is one of Scripture&apos;s great definitions of leadership. Not strength, not height, not military prowess, not cleverness. A heart that seeks God&apos;s will, that yields to God&apos;s word, that obeys even when the moment demands disobedience. This is what the Lord seeks in a king.",
