    "description": "The Hebrew suggests not merely that Jonathan&apos;s physical eyes opened, but that his understanding was illuminated. To eat the honey is to taste sweetness—and in that sweetness, something clarifies. The eyes of the soul brighten. Nourishment and revelation come together in a single act.",
    "bookSlug": "1-samuel",
    "chapter": 14,
    "language": "hebrew"
