    "title": "חֲרָדָה \"Trembling\" — The Fear of the Lord",
    "description": "What Jonathan and his armorbearer have set in motion is not a physical rout but a spiritual collapse. Trembling spreads—charadah, a word that speaks of the fear that comes when humans touch something beyond themselves. The Philistines are trembling because they have met the God of Israel, not merely a young prince.",
