    "title": "Cherem — Devoted Destruction",
    "description": "Cherem is the strongest form of destruction in Hebrew — not mere killing, but the utter annihilation of a thing, set apart wholly to the Lord with nothing left for human use or profit. It was used when a city was taken in war and devoted to the Lord (Joshua 6:17–21). The command here is absolute: nothing and no one from Amalek is to be spared, nothing is to be taken for human use.",
    "bookSlug": "1-samuel",
