    "description": "The name Goliath may derive from a Hebrew root meaning to roll, to pass over, or to exile. Whether or not the etymology is certain, the text makes clear what Goliath is: a man so massive, so armored, so utterly dominant that he seems to have passed beyond the category of ordinary human. He is the exile from mercy.",
