    "description": "Jonathan asks David not only for kindness while Jonathan lives, but for a covenant loyalty that will extend to Jonathan&apos;s house forever. Chesed is not mere kindness — it is the binding loyalty that flows from covenant. It is the promise that what flows from Jonathan to David will flow backward, from David to Jonathan&apos;s family, long after Jonathan is dead. It is a promise that outlasts life.",
