    "description": "The name Abiathar means \"father of abundance\" or \"my father is great.\" He will become the high priest in David&apos;s service, and his line will continue. He is the sole survivor of the Nob massacre. The name carries a quiet irony: from a family now orphaned, a man whose father and brothers are dead, he will go on to serve the Lord&apos;s anointed.",
