    "title": "Philadelphia — &ldquo;Brotherly Love&rdquo;",
    "description": "Philadelphia is the affection that binds siblings together—warm, particular, exclusive in a good way. It is not the love of strangers but the love of family. In the church, all believers are brothers and sisters, bound by Christ. See Hebrews 13:1; 1 Peter 1:22.",
