    "script": "ἄνομος",
    "translit": "<strong>anomos</strong> · lawless; transgressor; one who rejects divine authority",
    "title": "Anomos — Without Law, Lawless",
    "description": "The law was given to restrain the lawless and guide the wandering. It addresses those who actively rebel against God&apos;s order. The righteous—those already transformed by grace—live from a different motive: love, not law.",
