    "translit": "<strong>paradidōmi tō Satanǎ</strong> · deliver over to Satan; commit to Satan&apos;s domain",
    "title": "Delivered unto Satan",
    "description": "This is Paul&apos;s language of church discipline. Those who reject Christ and His truth are not protected by the church&apos;s spiritual covering. They are delivered to consequences—presumably so that hardship might teach them to \"learn not to blaspheme.\" This is discipline meant ultimately for restoration, not for permanent condemnation.",
    "bookSlug": "1-timothy",
    "chapter": 1,
    "language": "greek"
