    "translit": "<strong>sophrosynē</strong> · soundness of mind; self-control; sobriety; temperance",
    "title": "Sophrosynē — \"Sobriety\"",
    "description": "To be sophron is to have a sound mind—to be clear, sober, self-controlled. It is the opposite of being carried away by passion, consumed by desire to impress, or lost in vanity. It is the inner discipline that shows up in your outer choices.",
