    "title": "Tziyon — \"Sion\"",
    "description": "Mount Sion is not merely a geographical location but a spiritual reality—the dwelling place of God, the city of the redeemed, the seat of God&apos;s reign. In the New Testament, Revelation locates it at the end of all time: \"Mount Sion, and with him an hundred forty and four thousand\" (Revelation 14:1).",
