    "title": "Theodokia—\"Justification of God\"",
    "description": "The word \"theodicy\" comes from theo (God) and dikia (justice). To ask \"Why does God allow this?\" is to engage in the ancient task of theodicy—defending God&apos;s justice when the world appears unjust. 2 Esdras is a masterpiece of theodicy, not because it resolves the question easily, but because it refuses to.",
