    "title": "&apos;Arum — \"Subtil\"; Cunning Without Conscience",
    "description": "The same word describes the serpent in Genesis 3:1 (\"Now the serpent was more subtil than any beast of the field\"). It describes cleverness untethered from righteousness. Jonadab&apos;s counsel will not be wise counsel. It will be counsel designed to exploit Amnon&apos;s desire and turn it into action.",
    "bookSlug": "2-samuel",
