    "translit": "<strong>Banui</strong> · banished, exiled, driven away",
    "title": "Banished — בָּנוּי",
    "description": "The word carries the sense of one cast out, separated from home and family. It is the condition of Absalom — and the woman has named it plainly. The king \"doth not fetch home again his banished.\" She is speaking directly to David's unspoken wound.",
