    "title": "God Devises — חָשַׁב",
    "description": "God devises means. He plans. He schemes (in the good sense) so that His banished shall not be expelled. This is one of the most remarkable statements in Scripture about God's nature — not that He demands, but that He devices, plots, creates pathways for return. The word suggests creativity, intention, deliberate action toward restoration.",
    "bookSlug": "2-samuel",
    "chapter": 14,
    "language": "hebrew"
