    "script": "גָנַב",
    "translit": "<strong>Ganav</strong> · to steal, to pilfer, to take secretly",
    "title": "גָנַב (Ganav) — \"To Steal\" or \"To Pilfer\"",
    "description": "The text will soon say Absalom \"stole the hearts of the men of Israel.\" The word is not \"won\" or \"gained,\" but \"stole\" — as though he is a thief in the night, taking what belongs to his father. Flattery is theft. It takes without asking.",
    "bookSlug": "2-samuel",
    "chapter": 15,
    "language": "hebrew"
