    "description": "Shimei calls David a \"bloody man\" — ish damim. He is referencing David&apos;s many wars, his victories, his enemies slain. Shimei sees in David a killer, a man whose hands are stained with death. And in one sense, Shimei is not wrong. David has shed blood. But Shimei is also blind — he sees only the killing, not the justice; only the victory, not the anointing; only the crown, not the God who placed it.",
