    "title": "Chafed in Their Minds — Desperate, Angry",
    "description": "David and his men are not just tired — they are emotionally raw. They are like a bear robbed of her cubs, dangerous because they have nothing left to lose. Hushai reminds Absalom that desperation makes David and his followers more dangerous, not less.",
