    "title": "Mahanaim — \"Two Camps\"",
    "description": "Mahanaim is historically a boundary city, a place between kingdoms. In Genesis, Jacob sees it as a place of divine protection — the camp of God meeting the camp of Jacob. Now David, fleeing his own son, comes to the same refuge. The name carries a kind of duality: the camp of the fugitive king and the camp of God, standing together.",
