    "title": "Absalom — \"Father of Peace\"",
    "description": "The name is bitter irony itself. Absalom means \"father of peace,\" yet he has brought war. He sought to steal the throne and shatter the kingdom. And now, in his moment of capture, the name mocks him — he is the father of nothing but bloodshed, the bringer of anything but peace.",
