    "title": "The Wood of Ephraim",
    "description": "A wild, thickly wooded region east of the Jordan. The terrain itself becomes an enemy here — dense growth, tangled branches, a place where an army cannot maneuver. When the kingdom is in revolt, even creation conspires against the rebel. The wood does not care which side wins; it simply swallows soldiers whole.",
