    "title": "Absalom's Pillar — The Monument to Futility",
    "description": "A monument raised to preserve a name. Absalom built it because he had no sons to carry his name forward. He wanted to be remembered. But what is he remembered for? For this — for a pillar that marks the place of his death, for a moment when a king wept instead of celebrating. Not the legacy he imagined.",
