    "title": "Maschal — Burden; Also: Dominion",
    "description": "Barzillai says he does not wish to be \"yet a burden\" unto the king. The word carries the weight of genuine humility — not false modesty, but an honest reading of what an old man at court would be: someone who needs care, someone who consumes but cannot fully participate, someone who would sit at the table but not fully taste it.",
