    "title": "Evel — Mourning",
    "description": "Evel in Hebrew is not quiet sadness. It is public, performed, embodied grief. To be in evel is to wear it, to live it, to make it visible. David&apos;s evel is so complete that it swallows the kingdom. A king who mourns so openly that his victory becomes invisible.",
    "bookSlug": "2-samuel",
