    "title": "Bone and Flesh — Covenant Language",
    "description": "When David says \"Ye are my brethren, ye are my bones and my flesh,\" he is using the language of covenant. Not mere politics or strategy — but familial bond. Yet he is also testing that bond. The men of Judah are his \"bone and flesh,\" yet he doubts their allegiance? And Amasa is \"of my bone and my flesh,\" yet David did not see his own heart?",
