    "title": "Belial — \"Worthlessness\" (בְּלִיַּעַל)",
    "description": "The word does not name a demon, but a condition — a state of moral emptiness, a man without worth or restraint. Sheba is \"a man of Belial\" not because he serves a dark master, but because he is unmoored from any tether to loyalty or truth. His rebellion will come from nothing but his own grasping.",
