    "translit": "<strong>Kaphar</strong> · to cover; to atone; to make expiation",
    "title": "Kaphar — \"To Cover\" or \"To Atone\"",
    "description": "The word kaphar carries the sense of covering over, of wiping clean, of making restitution for a breach. Atonement is not forgetting the wrong; it is actively covering it, addressing it, restoring balance. David will seek to kaphar — to atone — for Saul&apos;s crime.",
    "bookSlug": "2-samuel",
