    "translit": "<strong>Qvurah</strong> · burial; sepulcher; the act of caring for the dead",
    "title": "Qvurah — \"Burial\" or \"Grave\"",
    "description": "In Scripture, qvurah — proper burial — is an act of covenant love. To bury someone is to honor them. To leave bodies unburied is the worst curse. David&apos;s decision to gather the remains and bury them properly, even those of Saul&apos;s sons who were hanged for his crime, shows that justice and honor need not exclude each other.",
    "bookSlug": "2-samuel",
