    "translit": "<strong>Chesed</strong> · mercy; lovingkindness; covenant loyalty; the steadfast commitment to those you have covenanted with",
    "title": "Chesed — \"Mercy\" or \"Covenant Loyalty\"",
    "description": "Chesed is not merely mercy in the sense of forgiveness. It is the active, ongoing commitment to the covenant. When God shows chesed to His anointed, He is renewing His promise, maintaining His oath, keeping faith with the one He has chosen. It is the love that lasts when all reasons to love have passed away.",
    "bookSlug": "2-samuel",
