    "translit": "<strong>Metsudah</strong> · fortress; stronghold; a place of safety with military capacity",
    "title": "Metsudah — \"Fortress\"",
    "description": "A metsudah is more than walls — it is a position of strength from which a garrison can withstand siege and launch sorties. When David calls God his metsudah, he is saying: I am not merely safe; I am empowered. I can stand against the flood.",
