    "title": "Ner — \"Lamp\" or \"Light\"",
    "description": "A ner is more intimate than a general light. It is the lamp that stands in a home, the light that allows you to see your way. It is not the distant sun; it is the fire kept burning in the house. When David calls God his ner, he is claiming not an abstract cosmic principle, but an intimate, present light that guides his steps.",
