    "translit": "<strong>Qarah</strong> · to call; to cry out; to invoke",
    "title": "Qarah — \"Called\" or \"Cried Out\"",
    "description": "Qarah is the verb of petition and invocation. It is how men call to their God in extremity, the cry that rises from the depths. Throughout the Psalms, qarah is the word that names the moment when a person ceases to rely on their own strength and calls upon the Lord. It is not a quiet prayer; it is a shout from the drowning.",
