    "script": "Ἑλληνιστής",
    "translit": "<strong>hellenistes</strong> · a Greek-speaking Jew; one influenced by Greek culture",
    "title": "Hellenistes — Greek-Speaking Jews",
    "description": "The \"Grecians\" are Hellenistic Jews—Greek-speaking, educated in Greek philosophy and culture, often more open to the world than the Hebrew-speaking Jews. Saul, who was educated at the feet of Gamaliel, is equipped to argue with them on their own terms. His conversion makes him a powerful advocate against those who would oppose the gospel in philosophical terms.",
    "bookSlug": "acts",
    "chapter": 9,
    "language": "greek"
