    "translit": "<strong>cheir</strong> · hand; a metonym for power, action, authority",
    "title": "Chēr — Grace; Hand; Power of the Lord",
    "description": "The hand of the Lord is a biblical image for God&apos;s active, powerful presence. It was with the prophets. It was with Jesus. Now it is with the scattered believers in Antioch. God is not abandoning the movement—He is expanding it.",
