    "script": "שָׁמַיִם",
    "translit": "<strong>shamayim</strong> · the heavens; the sky; height",
    "title": "Shamayim — &ldquo;heaven&rdquo;",
    "description": "Cities walled up to heaven are cities that seem impregnable, untouchable, beyond human capacity to overcome. The rhetoric is: these enemies are too great. But the next verse says God goes before as a consuming fire. What is impossible for Israel is routine for the Lord.",
