    "title": "Berakhah and Qelalah — Blessing and Curse",
    "description": "Berakhah carries the weight of all God&apos;s covenantal favor—multiplication, fruitfulness, protection. Qelalah is the withdrawal of that favor—barrenness, vulnerability, abandonment. They are absolute opposites, and the reader must choose which one their obedience will invoke.",
