    "script": "אֱלֹהִים",
    "translit": "<strong>elohim</strong> · gods, divine beings, or judges",
    "title": "Elohim — &ldquo;gods&rdquo;",
    "description": "The term can mean false gods or other divine powers. The law forbids worship directed to anything other than the Lord alone.",
