    "translit": "<strong>tamim</strong> · whole, complete, without blemish, single-eyed",
    "title": "Tamim — &ldquo;perfect, whole, complete&rdquo;",
    "description": "The word means integrity, undivided allegiance. Not perfection in morality, but wholeness—an eye that is single, a heart that is not split between God and the spirits, between the Lord and the hidden voices.",
