    "translit": "<strong>&apos;ed</strong> · a witness, one who testifies; literally, \"one who stands by and sees\"",
    "title": "\"Ed — \"Witness\"",
    "description": "A witness is one who has seen and can speak to what they saw. The weight of justice rests on the accuracy of that testimony. If that testimony is false, the one who would be innocent dies instead. This is why perjury carries the same weight as the crime itself.",
