    "title": "Shogeg — \"Ignorantly, Without Intention\"",
    "description": "Shogeg is the opposite of <em>zimam</em> (deliberate, premeditated). The law is built on the distinction between what you meant to do and what happened anyway. Intention matters because it reveals the heart.",
