    "translit": "<strong>bekhor</strong> · the firstborn, the eldest son",
    "title": "\"Firstborn\" — a right by birth, not feeling",
    "description": "The firstborn&apos;s right is a legal right, not a reward for being favored. A man might prefer his beloved wife&apos;s son, but the law strips preference away. The firstborn of any mother gets the double portion. The law protects the firstborn from paternal whim.",
