    "title": "Ets — \"tree\"",
    "description": "The word is simple—ets, a tree. A piece of wood becomes the instrument of public execution and shame. The body is left exposed, a sign of ultimate disgrace, and this exposure defiles the land itself. Only burial—and burial the same day—can remove the defilement.",
