    "translit": "<strong>qelalah</strong> · a curse, something cursed, accursed",
    "title": "Qelalah — the curse",
    "description": "To be hanged is to be cursed—utterly cut off, outside the covenant, receiving the final judgment of the community. Yet this curse itself becomes the foundation of the gospel.",
