    "translit": "<strong>toevah</strong> · something detestable; a violation of order",
    "title": "Toevah — \"abomination\"",
    "description": "The word does not mean merely \"disliked.\" It refers to what violates the created order — like mixing kinds of animals or seeds. God has made categories good; blurring them is a kind of chaos.",
