    "translit": "<strong>mamzer</strong> · one born of forbidden union",
    "title": "Mamzer — &ldquo;bastard&rdquo;",
    "description": "The mamzer bore the community&apos;s shame, not out of malice, but because bloodline mattered for inheritance and priestly service. Yet God&apos;s grace runs through the genealogies anyway — Ruth, Bathsheba, Rahab — all once outside, all brought in.",
