    "script": "חָרַשׁ",
    "translit": "<strong>charash</strong> · to be silent, still, to cease from labor",
    "title": "Charash — &ldquo;hold your peace&rdquo;",
    "description": "The root means both silence and the cessation of labor — to stop working. In this moment, Israel&apos;s work is to stop doing and start trusting. To be still is to hand over the fight to God. This is the hardest work there is.",
