    "translit": "<strong>man</strong> (from <strong>mah hu</strong>, &ldquo;what is it?&rdquo;)",
    "title": "Man — &ldquo;what is it?&rdquo;",
    "description": "When the Israelites first see the flakes on the ground, their question becomes the bread&apos;s name. They do not know what it is. God uses their confusion as a name: What Is It. Every time they eat it, they are remembering that they did not earn it, do not understand it, and cannot control it. Only receive it.",
    "bookSlug": "exodus",
