    "translit": "<strong>ephod</strong> · a linen garment with shoulder pieces",
    "title": "Ephod — &ldquo;priestly vest&rdquo;",
    "description": "The ephod is the primary garment of the high priest. The two shoulder stones inscribed with the names of the twelve tribes turn the priest himself into a living memorial before God.",
