    "translit": "<strong>ephod</strong> · bearing; carrying",
    "title": "Ephod — the priestly vest",
    "description": "The ephod means \"bearing\" or \"carrying.\" Worn by the priest, it displays the twelve tribal names on its shoulders. A priest&apos;s job is literally to carry the people.",
