    "translit": "<strong>tamid</strong> · continual, constant, perpetual",
    "title": "Tamid — the continual",
    "description": "The word means \"always\" or \"continuously.\" The offering does not end at sunset or when the priest grows tired. It is the rhythm that holds the whole system together — morning and evening, every day, without ceasing.",
