    "script": "קְטֹרֶת",
    "translit": "<strong>ketoret</strong> · smoke; burnt offering; the fragrant offering that rises upward",
    "title": "Ketoret — &ldquo;incense&rdquo;",
    "description": "Ketoret is the general word for incense, but also for any sweet-smelling offering. In Revelation 8:3, the angel at the altar holds ketoret — the prayers of the saints rising as incense before God.",
    "bookSlug": "exodus",
    "chapter": 30,
    "language": "hebrew"
