    "script": "זָהָב",
    "translit": "<strong>zahav</strong> · precious metal, the treasure; also means \"to shine\"",
    "title": "Zahav — &ldquo;gold&rdquo;",
    "description": "Gold beaten thin and woven into the work—not as weight, but as light. The priests who wear this will move, and the gold will catch the lamplight. Every movement of the priestly work is a kind of shining.",
