    "translit": "<strong>speirō</strong> · to sow; to plant; to scatter seed; to scatter broadcast",
    "title": "Speirō — To Sow; To Plant; To Scatter Seed",
    "description": "Sowing is deliberate. You choose what you plant. You choose where you plant it. You choose how you tend it. And then the harvest comes, not by magic, but by the nature of seed: corn produces corn, wheat produces wheat. What you plant grows.",
