    "description": "A stigma is a mark, usually a scar or a brand burned into flesh. In ancient times, a slave would be marked to show ownership. Paul bears the marks of Jesus—the scars of beatings, whippings, suffering. He is marked as Christ&apos;s possession, Christ&apos;s slave. It is his honor.",
