    "title": "Therizō — To Reap; To Harvest; To Gather",
    "description": "The reap follows the sow. This is not punishment; it is consequence, the nature of farming. The farmer does not reap because he deserves it; he reaps because he planted. So too: whatever you have planted in your life, you will harvest.",
