    "title": "Thlipsis — Persecution; Pressure; Tribulation",
    "description": "The false teachers are trying to avoid thlipsis—they want to be acceptable to the Jewish authorities, to avoid arrest or social shame. But Christ&apos;s followers cannot avoid it. The cross is a scandal. Believers will be pressured, mocked, worse. To glory in the cross is to accept that cost.",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapter": 6,
    "language": "greek"
