    "title": "Ezer kenegdo - &ldquo;help meet for him&rdquo;",
    "description": "The word <em>ezer</em> sounds gentle in English but is a strong word in Hebrew. It is used twice of Eve and twenty more times in the Old Testament - most often of God Himself, the &ldquo;helper&rdquo; of His people in battle (Ex. 18:4, Deut. 33:7, Ps. 33:20). <em>Kenegdo</em> means &ldquo;corresponding to, opposite, matching.&rdquo; Eve is not a subordinate; she is a strong companion who fits Adam exactly. The first marriage is two strengths meeting.",
