    "translit": "<strong>ish</strong> · man / <strong>isshah</strong> · woman",
    "title": "Ish · Isshah - &ldquo;man · woman&rdquo;",
    "description": "Until now the man has been <em>adam</em> (earthling). When the woman appears he speaks for the first time and gives them both new names: <em>ish</em> and <em>isshah</em> - words that share a root, that mirror each other in sound. He is naming her not as below him but as <em>like</em> him. The first poetry in the Bible is a love song. The first thing the man does with his voice is praise.",
