    "description": "The same phrase is used in Genesis 1:20 of fish and birds. Humans are not less embodied than animals - we are dust + breath, body and soul together. Greek philosophy will later treat the soul as a prisoner inside the body; the Hebrew Bible treats them as a single thing. You are not a soul that has a body. You are a living, breathing person.",
