    "translit": "<strong>shabat</strong> · to cease, to stop, to keep sabbath",
    "title": "Shabbat - &ldquo;ceased, kept sabbath&rdquo;",
    "description": "The Hebrew verb behind &ldquo;rested&rdquo; is not <em>nuach</em> (to relax) but <em>shabat</em> (to cease). Sabbath is not God catching His breath; it is God laying His tools down because the work is good and complete. Every weekly Sabbath since is the people of God agreeing with Him: <em>this is enough.</em>",
