    "title": "Qayin - \"gotten\"",
    "description": "The verb \"to get, to acquire\" (qanah) sounds like the name Cain (Qayin). Eve names her firstborn with a wordplay: \"I have gotten a man with the help of the LORD.\" The same name will carry a darker meaning when Cain murders - he \"gets\" his brother&apos;s life.",
