    "title": "Tsa&apos;aq - \"crieth\"",
    "description": "The same verb is used elsewhere for the cry of the oppressed reaching God&apos;s ears (Exodus 3:7). Abel&apos;s blood does not lie silent. It speaks. It calls. It demands acknowledgment from the God who made both brothers.",
