    "script": "בְנֵי־אֱלֹהִים",
    "translit": "<strong>b&apos;nei elohim</strong> · literally \"sons of God\"",
    "title": "Sons of God - בְנֵי־אֱלֹהִים",
    "description": "This phrase appears five times in the Old Testament. In Job 1:6 and 2:1 it refers to heavenly beings standing before God. Here the text names an intrusion-something stepping into the human order that was not human. Whether angel or priest, the crossing of a boundary is the point.",
