    "translit": "<strong>moreh</strong> · oak, terebinth (a large, distinctive tree)",
    "title": "Moreh - &ldquo;the oak of Moreh&rdquo;",
    "description": "The plain of Moreh is marked by an ancient oak tree, a landmark that would have been visible from far away. Later, other biblical leaders will stand at sacred oaks to renew covenant. Here, at the oak of Moreh, Abram enters the land God promised.",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
    "chapter": 12,
