    "script": "נָשָׂא עֵינַיִם",
    "translit": "<strong>nasa&apos; eynayim</strong> · lifted up the eyes; looked about; perceived",
    "title": "Nasa&apos; Eynayim - &ldquo;lifted up his eyes&rdquo;",
    "description": "This same idiom appears twice in Genesis 13: Lot lifts his eyes toward Sodom (v.10), and God tells Abram to lift his eyes and look in every direction (v.14). The same verb, the same act of seeing - but seeing toward different destinations, with different eyes.",
