    "translit": "<strong>El</strong> (God) · <strong>Elyon</strong> (most high, supreme)",
    "title": "El Elyon - &ldquo;God Most High&rdquo;",
    "description": "Melchizedek calls God by a title no one else in Genesis has used - the God who is above all other powers, all other claims, all other authority. In Abram&apos;s ears, a Canaanite priest is declaring a God higher than any in the pantheon of Canaan.",
