    "translit": "<strong>karat</strong> berit · literally \"to cut a covenant\"; berit = covenant",
    "title": "Karat Berit - \"to cut a covenant\"",
    "description": "The Hebrew idiom for making a covenant is to cut it. The covenant is not signed or sealed like a document. It is enacted through the cutting of animals, through blood and death. God&apos;s promise to Abram is not a contract. It is a death. It is a covenant written in animal blood, and Abram will understand that something as real as death stands behind every word God has spoken.",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
