    "title": "Mahanaim - &ldquo;two camps&rdquo;",
    "description": "Jacob sees the angels and names the place Mahanaim, &ldquo;two camps,&rdquo; because he has encountered God&apos;s army. The place will haunt Jacob this entire chapter. He himself will soon divide into two camps out of fear. And later, wrestling with the Man by night, he will be broken and remade - a splitting apart that leads to wholeness. The name Mahanaim echoes through the narrative, a constant reminder that God&apos;s presence is there, even in Jacob&apos;s terror.",
