    "script": "פְּנִיאֵל",
    "translit": "<strong>peniel</strong> · the face or presence of God",
    "title": "Peniel - &ldquo;face of God&rdquo;",
    "description": "The place is named Peniel, from <em>panim</em> (face) and <em>El</em> (God). Jacob has seen the face of God. Not in vision, not in prayer, but in the flesh - a physical encounter. His life is preserved. The name marks the place where the boundary between visible and invisible, known and mysterious, was torn open.",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
