    "description": "The oak itself is a memorial to grief. In later Jewish tradition, Deborah&apos;s burial here becomes a place of pilgrimage and prayer. A death at a threshold - a death at Bethel, where God meets His people - becomes a place where others come to remember and to grieve.",
