    "title": "Edom - &ldquo;red&rdquo;",
    "description": "The name recalls Genesis 25:30, where Esau sells his birthright for red lentil stew - \"give me, I pray thee, of that red pottage.\" Edom, red, echoes that moment of exchange, of choosing the visible and immediate over the unseen promise. The geography carries the memory of the choice.",
