    "script": "כֶּסֶף",
    "translit": "<strong>kesef</strong> · silver; blood money",
    "title": "Kesef - \"silver\" (also bloodshed)",
    "description": "The Hebrew word <em>kesef</em> means both silver and the spilling of blood. Reuben says, &ldquo;lay no hand upon him&rdquo; - do not shed blood. But the text is already whispering what will happen when the blood-silver and the brothers' hands meet again.",
