    "translit": "<strong>kesef</strong> · silver; twenty pieces",
    "title": "Kesef - \"twenty pieces of silver\"",
    "description": "The same word echoes across centuries. Judas will later be promised thirty pieces of silver for Jesus. Joseph is sold for twenty - the younger beloved son, betrayed by jealousy and greed. The number changes, but the story becomes a mirror.",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
    "chapter": 37,
    "language": "hebrew"
