    "script": "כְּתֹנֶת פַּסִּים",
    "translit": "<strong>ketonet passim</strong> · long-sleeved or ornamented robe",
    "title": "Ketonet Passim - \"coat of many colors\"",
    "description": "The same phrase is used of Tamar's royal robe in 2 Samuel 13:18. This is not a child's plaything - it is an aristocratic garment, the kind worn by the privileged, the kind that marks you as set apart. Jacob is not being sentimental; he is publicly announcing which son will inherit.",
