    "script": "רָעֶה",
    "translit": "<strong>ra&apos;eh</strong> · to shepherd, to pasture, to tend flocks",
    "title": "Ra&apos;eh - \"shepherd\"",
    "description": "The Egyptians despised shepherds. Shepherding was seen as a contemptible occupation in Egyptian culture - yet Joseph instructs his brothers to tell Pharaoh exactly what they are. They will not hide. They will not pretend. They will be themselves, even in a foreign kingdom.",
