    "title": "Aryeh - &ldquo;lion&rdquo;",
    "description": "Judah is named the lion - a symbol of strength and royal power. Two thousand years later, Revelation will echo this exact phrase: \"the Lion of the tribe of Juda hath prevailed\" (Rev. 5:5). The image is never forgotten.",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
