    "script": "אַסִּר חֲמוֹר לַגֶּפֶן",
    "translit": "<strong>assir chamor lagepen</strong> · binding a foal to the vine",
    "title": "Assir - &ldquo;binding the foal to the vine&rdquo;",
    "description": "This poetic image describes abundance: the vine is so fruitful that you can afford to tie your donkey to it. (Normally a vine is precious; an animal would eat it.) In Matthew 21, when Jesus rides into Jerusalem on a donkey (the foal of an ass), the people greet him with branches - echoing this image of the King coming in gentleness and plenty.",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
