    "script": "נָחָשׁ",
    "translit": "<strong>nakhash</strong> · serpent; also (as a verb) to hiss, to practice divination, to deceive",
    "title": "Nakhash - &ldquo;serpent&rdquo; (again)",
    "description": "This is the same root as in Genesis 3:1 - the serpent in the garden. The association is ominous. Dan&apos;s judgment will be subtle, dangerous, possibly deceptive.",
