    "script": "עֲצָמוֹת",
    "translit": "<strong>atsamot</strong> · bones",
    "title": "Atsamot - &ldquo;bones&rdquo;",
    "description": "Joseph's bones become a sign of faith. Moses will carry them out of Egypt (Exodus 13:19), and Joshua will bury them in Shechem (Joshua 24:32) - a fulfillment of this oath, centuries later. Bones are the hardest part of the body; they persist when everything else decays. Joseph's bones are his faith made flesh.",
