    "script": "חָשַׁב",
    "translit": "<strong>chashav</strong> · to think, plan, intend, reckon",
    "title": "Chashav - &ldquo;thought, intended, reckoned&rdquo;",
    "description": "Verse 20 uses <em>chashav</em> twice in parallel: \"ye thought evil against me; but God <em>thought</em> it unto good.\" The same verb is used in Genesis 15:6 where \"Abram believed the LORD, and he counted it [<em>chashav</em>] to him for righteousness.\" What you intend for harm and what God reckons for salvation are two different accountings.",
