    "script": "חָמַד",
    "translit": "<strong>Chamad</strong> · to see; to look upon; to observe",
    "title": "Chamad — \"Behold\"",
    "description": "Habakkuk is forced to behold iniquity—he cannot look away. It is all around him. The word conveys not detached observation but painful, unavoidable witnessing.",
