    "script": "סֶלָה",
    "translit": "<strong>Selah</strong> · pause; interlude; possibly \"forever\"",
    "title": "Selah — \"Pause\"",
    "description": "The word \"Selah\" appears in the Psalms and here. Its meaning is uncertain, but it suggests a pause for meditation or a musical interlude—a moment to let the weight of what has been said sink in.",
