    "script": "חֲמוּדוֹת",
    "translit": "<strong>Chamudot</strong> · precious things; desires; treasures",
    "title": "Chamudot — \"Desire\"",
    "description": "The Hebrew word can mean both the objects of desire and the desires themselves. The Desire of All Nations is what every people and person ultimately seeks—fulfillment, meaning, salvation.",
