    "script": "שְׂאוֹר",
    "translit": "<strong>se&apos;or</strong> · leaven, ferment, corruption",
    "title": "Se&apos;or — \"leaven\"",
    "description": "The word is related to \"se&apos;ar,\" to rise. Leaven causes things to rise, to puff, to change their nature through chemical decay. It represents anything that makes an offering false.",
