    "title": "Chazaq — \"To Repair\" or \"To Strengthen\"",
    "description": "The word used throughout Nehemiah 3 for the builders&apos; work is \"chazaq\" — to strengthen, to make firm, to repair. It is the same root as the name Hezekiah, meaning \"God is strong.\" Every act of repair is an act of strengthening — not merely fixing what is broken, but making it stronger than before. The work of rebuilding is an act of faith in God&apos;s strength.",
