    "title": "Neged — \"Over Against\" or \"Opposite\"",
    "description": "The word \"neged\" carries the sense of face-to-face, directly across from, or in front of. When the builders work \"over against their own house,\" they are working in the place they see every day, the section whose strength directly affects their own safety. It is personal. It is intimate. It is the place where care and self-interest align.",
    "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
    "chapter": 3,
    "language": "hebrew"
