    "title": "Yirat Elohim — \"Fear of God\"",
    "description": "The phrase \"fear of God\" is not about terror; it is about reverence and alignment with the will of God. To walk in the fear of God is to order your life according to His character. Nehemiah invokes this not as a threat, but as a call: remember who you serve. Remember what God demands of you.",
    "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
    "chapter": 5,
    "language": "hebrew"
