    "title": "Zekhreini Leoni — \"Think Upon Me, My God, for Good\"",
    "description": "This phrase does not ask God to reward Nehemiah with wealth or honor. It asks God to remember him — to hold him in mind — for the good he has done. It is an appeal to God&apos;s justice and fairness. Nehemiah trusts that his faithfulness, his refusal to extract from the people, his bearing of their burden, is something God sees and will acknowledge.",
