    "title": "Melachah — \"Work\" or \"Task\"",
    "description": "The word Nehemiah uses is \"melachah\" — not mere labor or toil, but a task entrusted to you by God. It carries weight. It is sacred work. When Nehemiah says \"I am doing a great work,\" he means: this is not my own ambition. This is what God has given me to do. To abandon it would be to betray that trust.",
