    "title": "Emunat — \"Faithfulness\"",
    "description": "The Hebrew root refers not only to faith as belief but to faithfulness as a consistent orientation. Abraham&apos;s heart was \"emet\" — reliable, grounded, turned toward God. It is a word of substance, not of feeling. God does not choose based on emotion but on the reliability of the covenant partner.",
