    "title": "Gaon — \"Pride\" or \"Haughtiness\"",
    "description": "The Hebrew gaon can mean majesty or excellence when applied to God, but when applied to humans it carries the sense of arrogance, of the inflation of the self beyond its proper place. When humans \"deal in gaon,\" they are asserting themselves as though they were the measure of all things.",
