    "description": "The Hebrew shemitah, from the root meaning \"to send away\" or \"to let go,\" refers to the Sabbatical Year when debts are forgiven and the land is left fallow. It is an act of faith and of mercy — an acknowledgment that the land belongs to God, and that human debts, human cycles, are subject to a higher rhythm.",
