    "description": "The Hebrew azav, \"to forsake,\" is used throughout Scripture to describe what happens when God&apos;s people turn away. \"My God, why hast thou forsaken me?\" But here, it is inverted: we will not forsake you. We will not abandon the house of your presence. We choose fidelity. We choose to stay.",
