    "description": "The Hebrew root asaph, meaning to gather or collect, is also used of gathering and sealing a covenant. The priests and people \"gathered\" (assembled) and \"sealed\" (asaph) the covenant. It is a gathering that results in a binding agreement — individuals assembled into a unified body, their separate wills gathered into one.",
