    "description": "The Hebrew word alah refers both to a curse and to an oath — they are two sides of the same coin. To swear an oath is to invoke a curse upon yourself if you break it. The people are not entering into a casual agreement. They are entering into a binding pledge that carries weight, that has teeth.",
