    "translit": "<strong>Chanukkah</strong> · dedication; the act of consecrating",
    "title": "Chanukkah — \"Dedication\"",
    "description": "The word \"chanukkah\" (dedication) comes from \"chanakh,\" meaning to train or inaugurate. When you dedicate something, you set it apart for its intended purpose — you begin its true work. The dedication of the wall is not merely a celebration of engineering; it is the consecration of Jerusalem itself as a city holy to God.",
