    "script": "רִנָּה",
    "translit": "<strong>Rinnah</strong> · singing; cry of joy; a shout of jubilation",
    "title": "Rinnah — \"Singing\" or \"Cry of Joy\"",
    "description": "The Hebrew \"rinnah\" is not quiet. It is a cry, a shout, a jubilant noise. When the text says the joy was \"heard,\" it carries the sense of \"rinnah\" — an audible, unmistakable proclamation of gladness that carries across distance.",
