    "translit": "<strong>Todah</strong> · thanksgiving; gratitude; a thank-offering",
    "title": "Todah — \"Thanksgiving\"",
    "description": "The root \"todah\" (thanksgiving) carries both the feeling and the practice. A todah-offering in the temple was not a sin-offering or guilt-offering; it was pure gratitude transformed into ritual action. To give thanks is to acknowledge that what we have was given, not earned.",
