    "translit": "<strong>Zakar</strong> · to remember; to keep in mind; to hold as significant",
    "title": "Zakar — \"Remember\"",
    "description": "Three times in this chapter, Nehemiah will pray, \"Remember me, O my God.\" The word \"zakar\" is not merely a request to be kept in mind, but to be acted upon. To be remembered by God is to be sustained, to be vindicated, to be kept covenant with. Nehemiah stakes his hope not on the stability of his reforms, but on God&apos;s remembrance of his good deeds.",
