    "title": "Pequdim — &ldquo;those mustered&rdquo;",
    "description": "The root <em>paqad</em> means to number, to muster, to take account of. Not as cattle, but as warriors — a people with agency, called by name. The book itself is called <em>Bemidbar</em> in Hebrew, &ldquo;in the wilderness,&rdquo; but the English name comes from the numbering.",
