    "title": "Vidui — &ldquo;confession&rdquo;",
    "description": "The Hebrew root means to throw or cast — to cast forth the sin, to speak it aloud. Confession is not silent remorse. It is spoken, public, a declaration before God and witness that the wrong has been named.",
