    "title": "Me ha-Marim — &ldquo;waters of bitterness&rdquo;",
    "description": "The waters taste of judgment. They are described as causing a curse if guilt is found. Yet they are administered by God, not by the husband. The woman's innocence or guilt is revealed not by human judgment but by divine response. God is the only judge who can see what is hidden.",
