    "description": "Shalom is the goal-word of Hebrew blessing. It means far more than the absence of war; it means the presence of everything good — health, prosperity, harmony, justice, and the peace of knowing you belong to God. The priestly blessing ends not with a wish for comfort, but with the promise of <em>shalom</em> — the fullness of God&apos;s favor.",
