    "title": "Menorah — &ldquo;the seven lamps&rdquo;",
    "description": "The menorah[res:bible-odyssey-menorah] is a symbol of the presence of God and the light He sheds on His work. In Exodus 25, God instructs Israel to make it of pure gold, hammered thin—a single piece of metal shaped by hand, with the center lamp flanked by three branches on each side.",
