    "title": "Taavah — \"to lust, crave, desire\"",
    "description": "The root word for the place name. Taavah is not neutral desire; it is the hunger of the flesh that opposes the Spirit. It is craving untethered from gratitude, wanting untethered from obedience. It is the desire that says \"I deserve this\" and \"God is withholding from me.\"",
