    "description": "The go'el was a male relative obligated by law to help a family in distress—to redeem their land if sold, to provide an heir through levirate marriage if widowed, to avenge if wronged. Boaz will become Ruth's go'el, but not until chapter 4. For now, he exists in Naomi's hope.",
    "bookSlug": "ruth",
