    "title": "Gaal — &ldquo;to redeem&rdquo;",
    "description": "The kinsman-redeemer in Israel&apos;s law had the right — and responsibility — to buy back family land sold in hardship, and to marry the widow of a dead brother to raise up his name. The word carries the weight of family honor restored.",
    "bookSlug": "ruth",
