    "title": "Na&apos;al — &ldquo;shoe&rdquo;",
    "description": "The removal of the shoe was a public gesture of surrender — a man taking off his shoe and handing it over was saying, <em>I relinquish my claim.</em> The sandal remained in Israelite memory as a witness to the transaction.",
    "bookSlug": "ruth",
    "chapter": 4,
    "language": "hebrew"
