    "title": "Chrestotēs — Kindness",
    "description": "Kindness is not sentimental. It is the active disposition of God toward a rebellious humanity. He does not hate us for our malice. He shows kindness. He does good to those who deserve judgment. This kindness appears in history, in the incarnation, in the cross.",
