    "title": "Kleros — Heirs, Inheritance",
    "description": "A heir receives not because of merit but because of family relation. You are an heir not because you deserve it, but because you belong to the family of God through Christ. The inheritance is eternal life—not merely endless existence, but the endless communion with God that life was always meant to be.",
