    "description": "The word is rare in Scripture—used only here and in Acts 28:2 of ordinary human hospitality. Paul uses it of God Himself. God&apos;s philanthropia is His love for the human race as a whole. Not distant. Not impersonal. The love of God toward all humans, displayed in Christ.",
