    "title": "Shuv — \"Turn\" (Return)",
    "description": "The Hebrew word shuv is not merely a change of direction. It carries the sense of returning to a place, a person, or a state one has left. In repentance, it means returning to God. God uses this word to beckon Israel: turn back to Me, and I will turn to you. The mutuality here is striking—God&apos;s heart moves toward those whose hearts move toward Him.",
