    "title": "Tzoa — \"Filthy\"",
    "description": "The garments are not merely soiled—they are ritually filthy, unfit for the high priest to wear. The stripping away of these garments represents God&apos;s removal of Israel&apos;s sin and shame, a cleansing that goes beyond what human effort could accomplish.",
